    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-26T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-26T01:00:00-05:00" n="570"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12167: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Chefoo (<persName type="from">Webber</persName>)
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chefoo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-26T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 26, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 26—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following telegram has been sent this noon Legation at Peiping: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“September 26, noon. Dr. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BJ1"
                                >Beall</persName> of American Southern Baptist Mission<note n="81"
                                xml:id="d570fn81">At Laichow, Shantung Province.</note> called this
                            morning and informed me all mission property occupied upon their
                            evacuation and used by <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LC9"
                                >Liu</persName>’s forces as defense works, contents presumably
                            looted.</p>
                        <p>Owing to impossibility to get in communication with <persName
                                corresp="frus1932v03#p_LC9">Liu</persName> I suggest if possible
                            protest be made to Nanking Government who are reported to be in
                            communication with <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LC9">Liu</persName>
                            by wireless telegraph. Loss will run into thousands.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please inform American Southern Baptist Mission, Richmond, foregoing as well as
                    fact all their missionaries safe and are either at Hwanghsien or Chefoo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webber</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
